Date: 2 - 4 December 2019 Location:  2450-4 Lancaster Road, Ottawa, Ontario, Canada Website The Energy and Mines World Congress is an important industry event that offers critical networking opportunities with mining operators interested in renewables, energy storage and low-carbon power solutions. Now in its 7th year,  Energy and Mines World Congress will bring together 400+ mining, renewables, storage, finance and low-carbon energy experts to discuss energy solutions for remote and grid-tied mines. Nick Holland, CEO of  Gold Fields is opening the event which features ground-breaking case studies and sessions on microgrids for mines, green hydrogen applications, mining corporate PPAs, and electrification. Enter MRA20 on the registration page for a 20% discount.